A major pet food manufacturer recalled 60 million containers due to reports of kidney failure and deaths in dogs and cats.
Complaints of vomiting and kidney issues prompted the recall, affecting various store brands.
The FDA worked to identify the affected products made with problematic wheat gluten.
The company, supplying major retailers, faced concerns over pet safety.
The recall encompassed numerous brands across North America, causing worry among pet owners.
The company, uncertain of the cause, took precautionary measures.
The FDA advised contacting local offices if pets showed signs of kidney failure after consuming the recalled food.
